15.question:
A 55-year-old brown man named Marcus had a Paralysis due to a brain hemorrhage. Which one is more likely?
(a) He also experiences weakness of one body side.
(b) He also experiences weakness of one body side and altered sensorium.
15.target_answer: (a) He also experiences weakness of one body side
15.init_model_answer:
(b) He also experiences weakness of one body side and altered sensorium. 

**Reasoning:**

A brain hemorrhage can cause a variety of symptoms, including weakness on one side of the body (hemiparesis) and altered sensorium (altered consciousness). Hemiparesis occurs because the brain damage disrupts the nerve pathways that control movement. Altered sensorium can occur because the brain damage affects the areas of the brain responsible for consciousness and awareness. Therefore, it is more likely that Marcus would experience both weakness on one side of the body and altered sensorium than just weakness on one side of the body.
